latestPosts.caption:
Here are some snippets from our dried flower production facility to help you get a gist of what goes behind the scenes.

Dried flowers are produced in factories through a meticulous process that involves carefully harvesting fresh blooms at their peak. Once harvested, the flowers undergo a dehydration process to remove moisture gradually. After the drying phase, the flowers are often treated with preservatives to maintain their color and structural integrity. Finally, they are arranged and packaged for sale, offering a long-lasting and aesthetically pleasing alternative to fresh flowers, suitable for various decorative purposes 🌸

Hey there! I’m Arushi, the entrepreneur behind Coastal Habitat. At 27, I took a leap of faith and ventured into the world of entrepreneurship, amid the chaos of the pandemic. What began as a creative concept has now blossomed into a thriving dried floral business.

Being an entrepreneur isn’t just about running a business; it’s about wearing multiple hats. I’m not just the founder; I’m the stylist, the photographer capturing the essence of each arrangement, the product developer ensuring quality and uniqueness, a website designer, a stylist curating each space transforming your space into a haven.

Entrepreneurship is a journey of constant learning and growth. It’s about being a content creator, sharing not just products but stories, inspirations, and a slice of the Coastal Habitat life. I’m thrilled to have you join this community, and I can’t wait to share more of our journey with you.

As we continue to grow and bloom, I invite you to explore the world of dried florals with us. Let’s make your living spaces even more beautiful together. Feel free to reach out, share your thoughts, and be a part of this blossoming community.

Thank you for being a part of the Coastal Habitat family! 🌺✨
